-- Legal & General says to quit British insurance body ABI
-- By Nishant Kumar
-- Wed Aug 13, 2014 03:14AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, Aug 13 (Reuters) - Life insurance and pensions company Legal & General Group Plc <LGEN.L> will quit trade body Association of British Insurers (ABI), a spokesman said on Wednesday without giving reasons for the decision.

The 177-year-old company will release a statement later in the day giving details of its decision, the spokesman said.